  "chunks": [
    {
      "chunk_type": "isnad",
      "arabic_text": "اَلْحُسَيْنُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ عَنْ مُعَلَّى بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ عَنْ عَلِيِّ بْنِ أَسْبَاطٍ قَالَ:",
      "translations": {
        "en": "Al-Ḥusayn ibn Muḥammad, from Muʿallā ibn Muḥammad, from ʿAlī ibn Asbāṭ, who said:"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "opening",
      "arabic_text": "رَأَيْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ (عَلَيْهِ السَّلَامُ) وَقَدْ خَرَجَ عَلَيَّ، فَأَخَذْتُ النَّظَرَ إِلَيْهِ، وَجَعَلْتُ أَنْظُرُ إِلَى رَأْسِهِ وَرِجْلَيْهِ لِأَصِفَ قَامَتَهُ لِأَصْحَابِنَا بِمِصْرَ.",
      "translations": {
        "en": "I saw Abū Jaʿfar (عليه السلام) when he had come out to me, so I began looking at him, and I started looking at his head and his feet so that I might describe his stature to our companions in Miṣr."
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "body",
      "arabic_text": "فَبَيْنَا أَنَا كَذَلِكَ حَتَّى قَعَدَ، فَقَالَ: يَا عَلِيُّ، إِنَّ اللَّهَ احْتَجَّ فِي الْإِمَامَةِ بِمِثْلِ مَا احْتَجَّ بِهِ فِي النُّبُوَّةِ، فَقَالَ:",
      "translations": {
        "en": "While I was like that, he sat down and said: “O ʿAlī, indeed Allah has established the proof in the Imamate by the like of what He established the proof with in Prophethood, so He said:”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "quran_quote",
      "arabic_text": "﴿وَآتَيْنَاهُ الْحُكْمَ صَبِيًّا﴾",
      "translations": {
        "en": "“And We gave him judgment while yet a child.”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "quran_quote",
      "arabic_text": "﴿وَلَمَّا بَلَغَ أَشُدَّهُ وَبَلَغَ أَرْبَعِينَ سَنَةً﴾",
      "translations": {
        "en": "“And when he reached his maturity and reached forty years.”"
      }
    },
    {
      "chunk_type": "closing",
      "arabic_text": "فَقَدْ يَجُوزُ أَنْ يُؤْتَى الْحِكْمَةَ وَهُوَ صَبِيٌّ، وَيَجُوزُ أَنْ يُؤْتَاهَا وَهُوَ ابْنُ أَرْبَعِينَ سَنَةً.",
      "translations": {
        "en": "So it is possible for wisdom to be given while he is a child, and it is possible for it to be given to him while he is a son of forty years.”
      }
    }
  ],
  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "summary": "This hadith presents the Imam’s argument that divine designation in Imamate follows the same pattern as divine designation in Prophethood. By citing Quranic examples of wisdom granted in childhood and at forty years of age, it shows that age does not restrict Allah’s conferral of divine authority and wisdom.",
      "seo_question": "How does this hadith use the Quran to show that an Imam may be appointed at a young age?",
      "key_terms": {
        "الْإِمَامَةِ": "the divinely appointed office of the Imam",
        "النُّبُوَّةِ": "Prophethood as a parallel proof for divine appointment",
        "الْحُكْمَ": "judgment or divinely granted wisdom and authority",
        "صَبِيًّا": "in a state of childhood or young age",
        "أَشُدَّهُ": "full strength or maturity",
        "أَرْبَعِينَ سَنَةً": "forty years of age, indicating mature adulthood"
      }
    }
  },
